  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 8 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 8 high, 13 medium, 17 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Modlin (WMI/EPMO) and Kraków John Paul II (KRK/EPKK); plus 6 other bases. 13 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Václav Havel Airport Prague (PRG/LKPR) and London Luton (LTN/EGGW). Network hotspots: Shirak (LWN/UDSG), Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Tenerife Sur (TFS/GCTS) and 3 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, very low visibility and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Shirak (LWN/UDSG), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Almaty (ALA/UAAA) and 9 others.",
